text: Nina Taborsky (born April 28, 1978, Vienna) is an Austrian rhythmic gymnast. Taborsky competed for Austria in the rhythmic gymnastics individual all-around competition at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. There she was 29th in the qualification round and did not advance to the semifinal. == References == == External links == * * Category:1978 births Category:Living people Category:Austrian rhythmic gymnasts Category:Gymnasts at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gymnasts of Austria Category:Sportspeople from Vienna
